AB  - The prevalence of depression among adolescents has been steadily increasing in recent years. Exergames hold the potential to provide a positive entertainment experience, yet their utilization among adolescents with depression remains limited. This study aims to investigate the perceptions and requirements regarding exergames in adolescents with depression, with the goal of designing tailored exergame intervention programs for clinical applications.
