AB  - Black people in the United States have the highest rates of heart failure, and the worst outcomes of any racial/ethnic group which has been linked to both sociostructural (e.g. racism, poverty, food deserts) and behavioral factors. Physical activity is vital in managing heart failure, yet little is known about the perceptions of the Black community with heart failure. The purpose of this study was to understand and interpret physical activity engagement and the factors that may influence it in Black individuals with heart failure.
