AB  - Adaptive emotion regulation and physical activity may protect against mental health conditions such as depression and anxiety in adolescents. However, contextually relevant psychosocial interventions remain scarce in South Africa, and limited research explores adolescents' lived experiences and perceived impacts of these interventions. This qualitative study examined the feasibility, acceptability, and perceived impact of a co-adapted, task-shared emotion regulation intervention incorporating physical activity.
