AB  - The postpartum period, a time known to instil joy and fulfilment, is dominated by unreasonable and often unattainable expectations for mothers to achieve perfection across multiple domains. Despite prior research confirming that body image dissatisfaction, disordered eating and postpartum depression are prevalent in the postpartum, mothers remain pressured to maintain active and healthy lifestyles while juggling the demands of parenthood.
