AB  - The article looks at the factors influencing a patient's decision to return to his or her preinjury level of sport after anterior cruciate ligament (ACL) reconstruction. It cites the qualitative, semistructured interviews of 31 patients, aged 18 to 40 years, who had undergone primary ACL reconstruction surgery. It also indicates that fear, shifts in priority, and individual personalities influenced patients who did not return to their preinjury level of sport after primary ACL reconstruction.
