AB  - Postpartum depression is the most common mental health disorder associated with the birth of a child. However, postpartum depression often remains untreated because there are not enough prevention and treatment options. Barriers such as lack of knowledge and fear of stigmatization also make it more difficult for affected women to start treatment. Digital interventions could be an option which might circumvent many of these barriers. This study describes the development process of the smartphone-based intervention Smart-e-Moms which aims to reduce postpartum depressive symptoms.
