AB  - Racism can be stressful and can even be traumatizing. Psychological unwellness may result from a combination of historical, cultural, and individual experiences, resulting in syndromes that may or may not fit into the Diagnostic and Statistical Manual of Mental Disorders, fifth edition for posttraumatic stress disorder diagnostic framework but often meet the criteria for posttraumatic stress disorder. There are no validated treatment protocols for this constellation of symptoms called racial trauma. This case series describes the development and utilization of the Healing Racial Trauma Protocol for four people of color with clinically significant symptoms of racial trauma. This article reports the experiences of both participants and study therapists, along with a discussion of treatment challenges and future directions. (PsycInfo Database Record (c) 2025 APA, all rights reserved)
