AB  - Exercise has many health benefits whether it is anaerobic (Auchus & Kaslow 1994) or aerobic (Noreau 1995). The majority of health professionals and exercisers believe that exercise has benefits for the improvement of mood states, and mental health (Byrne & Byrne, 1993). 'This preliminary nursing research study confirms mood enhancement following exercise in a clinical sample. Qualitative and Quantitative methods were employed. The findings confirmed that anxiety and depression scores were reduced post-exercise. Analysis of Qualitative data also provided an understanding of the experience of exercise participation from the clients perspective. The themes identified were, immediate effects, locus of control, feeling of achievement, social support and self-esteem, general health, reflecting on the experience and body image. This initial study has important implications for developing new insights and innovative methods of mental health promotion in nursing practice.
