AB  - This narrative study examined how perceived encouragement during adolescence affects female career choice. Utilizing stories gathered through semistructured interviews, the researcher developed a definition of encouragement, examined covert and overt messages of encouragement, and identified individuals who provided encouragement to study participants. This study also identified factors that influenced participants’ career choices, examined career choice barriers, and identified factors that helped females overcome these barriers. (PsycInfo Database Record (c) 2025 APA, all rights reserved)
