AB  - Veterans’ religious and spiritual (R/S) struggles can negatively impact mental health, yet little is known about the range of R/S struggles veterans experience. In-depth qualitative interviews with 22 U.S. veterans were used to increase understanding of veterans’ R/S struggles across 6 domains: divine, demonic, interpersonal, moral, doubt, and ultimate meaning. Reported R/S struggles stemmed from both military and civilian experiences. Veterans described significant emotional pain and distress related to these struggles, highlighting the connection between spiritual and emotional well-being. Clinicians should inquire about veterans’ potential R/S struggles and explore how these struggles may relate to mental health and overall well-being. (PsycInfo Database Record (c) 2020 APA, all rights reserved)
